 (S)-2-amino-4-(D-glucopyranosyl)amino-4-oxobutanoic acid residue.\" [GOC:pr, RESID:AA0421]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents a molecular function.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid N-linked glucosylation via asparagine\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28482\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\ncreated_by: mah\ncreation_date: 2010-09-15T03:54:25Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0120532\nname: glycosaminoglycan-protein linkage region biosynthetic process\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The formation of a tetrasaccharide linker sequence (xylose-galactose-galactose-glucuronate) on specific serine residues of a core protein, on to which dermatan sulfate, chondroitin sulfate, heparan sulfate or heparin glycosaminoglycans may be assembled to synthesise the corresponding proteoglycan.\" [MetaCyc:PWY-6557]\nsynonym: \"Glycosaminoglycan biosynthesis, linkage tetrasaccharide\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"glycosaminoglycan-protein linkage region biosynthesis\" EXACT [MetaCyc:PWY-6557]\nxref: MetaCyc:PWY-6557\nis_a: GO:0180064 ! protein O-linked glycosylation via xylose\nrelationship: part_of GO:0015012 ! heparan sulfate proteoglycan biosynthetic process\nrelationship: part_of GO:0030210 ! heparin proteoglycan biosynthetic process\nrelationship: part_of GO:0050650 ! chondroitin sulfate proteoglycan biosynthetic process\nrelationship: part_of GO:0050651 ! dermatan sulfate proteoglycan biosynthetic process\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28977\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29294\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30378\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: sjm\ncreation_date: 2024-11-27T13:13:42Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140264\nname: keratan sulfate-II proteoglycan biosynthetic process\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of keratan sulfate II (KS-II), O-linked via a GalNAc attached to a serine or a threonine residue in the target protein.\" [PMID:29340594]\nsynonym: \"O-linked GalNAc-keratan sulfate-II proteoglycan biosynthetic process\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0016266 ! protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetyl-galactosamine\nis_a: GO:0018146 ! keratan sulfate proteoglycan biosynthetic process\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30595\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-07-23T09:39:41Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140265\nname: keratan sulfate-III proteoglycan biosynthetic process\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of keratan sulfate III (KS-III), O-linked via a mannose attached to a serine or a threonine residue in the target protein.\" [PMID:29340594]\nsynonym: \"O-linked man-keratan sulfate-III proteoglycan biosynthetic process\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0018146 ! keratan sulfate proteoglycan biosynthetic process\nis_a: GO:0035269 ! protein O-linked glycosylation via mannose\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30595\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-07-23T09:40:52Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0180057\nname: protein post-translational transfer of dolichol-linked oligosaccharide\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A N-linked protein glycosylation process in which the preassembled dolichol-linked oligosaccharide precursor is transfered co-translationally to an asparagine residue within the motif Asn-X-Ser/Thr of the target protein. This is mediated by the OSTB complex.\" [PMID:19167329]\nsynonym: \"protein N-linked glycosylation via asparagine, post-translational\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"protein N-linked glycosylation via asparagine, posttranslational\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"protein posttranslational transfer of dolichol-linked oligosaccharide\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0009101 ! glycoprotein biosynthetic process\nrelationship: part_of GO:0006487 ! protein N-linked glycosylation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30140\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30595\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: vw\ncreation_date: 2025-06-02T08:04:12Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0180058\nname: protein co-translational transfer of dolichol-linked oligosaccharide\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A N-linked protein glycosylation process in which the preassembled dolichol-linked oligosaccharide precursor is transfered post-translationally to an asparagine residue within the motif Asn-X-Ser/Thr of the target protein. This is mediated by the OSTA complex.\" [PMID:19167329]\nsynonym: \"protein cotranslational transfer of dolichol-linked oligosaccharide\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"protein N-linked glycosylation via asparagine, co-translational\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"protein N-linked glycosylation via asparagine, cotranslational\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0009101 ! glycoprotein biosynthetic process\nrelationship: part_of GO:0006487 ! protein N-linked glycosylation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30140\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30595\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: vw\ncreation_date: 2025-06-02T08:07:11Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0180059\nname: protein O-linked glycosylation via glucose\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A glycoprotein biosynthetic process starting with the covalent linkage of a glucose via a beta-glycosidic bond to the oxygen atom of a serine, threonine or tyrosine side chain in a protein, which can be further elongated with the sequential addition of sugar units resulting in the formation of a protein O-linked glycan.\" [PMID:35536928]\nsynonym: \"protein O-linked glucosylation\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0006493 ! protein O-linked glycosylation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29770\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30362\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30592\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: vw\ncreation_date: 2025-06-03T08:20:06Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0180062\nname: protein O-linked glycosylation via galactose\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A glycoprotein biosynthetic process starting with the covalent linkage of galactose via a beta-glycosidic bond to the oxygen atom of the hydroxyl group of a hydroxyproline, a hydroxylysine, a serine or a threonine in a protein, which can be further elongated with the sequential addition of sugar units resulting in the formation of a protein O-linked glycan. Hydroxylysine modification occurs in the endoplasmic reticulum and is predominantly found in collagen. Hydroxyproline modification occurs in the Golgi and is found only in plant proteins.\" [PMID:17516569, PMID:30822656, PMID:33815452]\nsynonym: \"protein O-linked galactosylation\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0006493 ! protein O-linked glycosylation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29770\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30362\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30592\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: vw\ncreation_date: 2025-06-03T08:25:18Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0180063\nname: protein O-linked glycosylation via arabinose\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A glycoprotein biosynthetic process starting with the covalent linkage of an arabinose via a beta-glycosidic bond to the oxygen atom of the hydroxyl group of a hydroxyproline in a protein, which can be further elongated with the sequential addition of sugar units resulting in the formation of a protein O-linked glycan.\" [PMID:33815452]\nsynonym: \"protein O-linked arabinosylation\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0006493 ! protein O-linked glycosylation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30362\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30592\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: vw\ncreation_date: 2025-06-03T13:24:19Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0180064\nname: protein O-linked glycosylation via xylose\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A glycoprotein biosynthetic process starting with the covalent linkage of a xylose via a beta-glycosidic bond to the oxygen atom of a serine or a threonine side chain in a protein, which can be further elongated with the sequential addition of sugar units resulting in the formation of a protein O-linked glycan.\" [PMID:22117070]\nsynonym: \"protein O-linked xylosylation\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0006493 ! protein O-linked glycosylation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30362\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30592\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: vw\ncreation_date: 2025-06-03T13:29:21Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:1904098\nname: regulation of protein O-linked glycosylation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein O-linked glycosylation.\" [GO_REF:0000058, GOC:TermGenie, PMID:24509081]\nsubset: gocheck_obsoletion_candidate\nsynonym: \"regulation of protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nintersection_of: GO:0065007 ! biological regulation\nintersection_of: regulates GO:0006493 ! protein O-linked glycosylation\ncreated_by: krc\ncreation_date: 2015-03-27T16:09:58Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:1904099\nname: negative regulation of protein O-linked glycosylation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein O-linked glycosylation.\" [GO_REF:0000058, GOC:TermGenie, PMID:24509081]\nsubset: gocheck_obsoletion_candidate\nsynonym: \"down regulation of protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"down regulation of protein O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"down-regulation of protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"down-regulation of protein O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"downregulation of protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"downregulation of protein O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"inhibition of protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation\" NARROW [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"inhibition of protein O-linked glycosylation\" NARROW [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"negative regulation of protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nintersection_of: GO:0065007 ! biological regulation\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates GO:0006493 ! protein O-linked glycosylation\ncreated_by: krc\ncreation_date: 2015-03-27T16:10:04Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:1904100\nname: positive regulation of protein O-linked glycosylation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein O-linked glycosylation.\" [GO_REF:0000058, GOC:TermGenie, PMID:24509081]\nsubset: gocheck_obsoletion_candidate\nsynonym: \"activation of protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation\" NARROW [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"activation of protein O-linked glycosylation\" NARROW [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"positive regulation of protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"up regulation of protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"up regulation of protein O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"up-regulation of protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"up-regulation of protein O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"upregulation of protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsynonym: \"upregulation of protein O-linked glycosylation\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nintersection_of: GO:0065007 ! biological regulation\nintersection_of: positively_regulates GO:0006493 ! protein O-linked glycosylation\ncreated_by: krc\ncreation_date: 2015-03-27T16:10:10Z\n\n","metadata":{"output":"...\n\n/30362\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30366\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30592\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0018240\nname: obsolete protein S-linked glycosylation via cysteine\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The glycosylation of protein via the sulfur atom of peptidyl-cysteine, forming S-glycosyl-L-cysteine.\" [RESID:AA0152]\ncomment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term represents a molecular function.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid S-linked glycosylation via cysteine\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-announcements/issues/988\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0018280\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0018241\nname: obsolete protein O-linked glycosylation via hydroxylysine\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The glycosylation of protein via the O5 atom of peptidyl-hydroxylysine, forming O5-glycosyl-L-hydroxylysine; the most common form is galactosyl hydroxylysine.\" [RESID:AA0153]\ncomment: for obsoletion is that this term represents a molecular function.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation via hydroxylysine\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-announcements/issues/988\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0018242\nname: obsolete protein O-linked glycosylation via serine\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The glycosylation of protein via the O3 atom of peptidyl-serine, forming O3-glycosyl-L-serine; the most common forms are N-acetylgalactosaminyl, mannosyl, galactosyl, and xylosyl serine.\" [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK579918/]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it did not represent a specific process. It may correspond to protein O-linked galactosylation; GO:0180062, protein O-linked xylosylation ; GO:0180064, protein O-linked glucosylation ; GO:0180059, and protein O-linked GFucNAcylation, all of which may be linked to a serine in a protein.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation via serine\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30517\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nconsider: GO:0180059\nconsider: GO:0180062\nconsider: GO:0180064\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0018243\nname: obsolete protein O-linked glycosylation via threonine\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The glycosylation of protein via the O3 atom of peptidyl-threonine, forming O3-glycosyl-L-threonine; the most common forms are N-acetylgalactosaminyl, mannosyl, and galactosyl threonine.\" [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK579918/]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it did not represent a specific process. It may correspond to protein O-linked GalNAcylation ; GO:0016266, protein O-linked glucosylation ; GO:0180059, protein O-linked galactosylation; GO:0180062, or protein O-linked mannosylation ; GO:0035269, all of which may be linked to a threonine in a protein.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation via threonine\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30517\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nconsider: GO:0016266\nconsider: GO:0035269\nconsider: GO:0180059\nconsider: GO:0180062\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0018244\nname: obsolete protein N-linked glycosylation via tryptophan\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The glycosylation of protein via peptidyl-tryptophan, 1'-glycosyl-L-tryptophan; results in the formation of an (S)-2-amino-3-(1-D-mannopyranosyloxy-1H-indol-3-yl)propanoic acid residue.\" [RESID:AA0156]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents a molecular function.\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-announcements/issues/822\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28482\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28538\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0006487\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0018245\nname: obsolete protein O-linked glycosylation via tyrosine\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The glycosylation of protein via the O4' atom of peptidyl-tyrosine, O4'-glycosyl-L-tyrosine; the carbohydrate is glucose, the origin for glycogen.\" [RESID:AA0157]\ncomment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term represents a molecular function.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation via tyrosine\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29770\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0018258\nname: obsolete protein O-linked glycosylation via hydroxyproline\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The glycosylation of proteins via 04 atom of hydroxyproline to form O4-glycosyl-L-hydroxyproline; the most common form is arabinofuranosyl-4-proline.\" [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK579918/]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it did not represent a specific process. It may correspond to protein O-linked GalNAcylation; GO:0016266, protein O-linked galactosylation; GO:0180062, or protein O-linked arabinosylation; GO:0180063, all of which may be linked to a hydroxyproline in a protein.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid O-linked glycosylation via hydroxyproline\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30517\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nconsider: GO:0016266\nconsider: GO:0180062\nconsider: GO:0180063\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0018279\nname: obsolete protein N-linked glycosylation via asparagine\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The glycosylation of protein via the N4 atom of peptidyl-asparagine forming N4-glycosyl-L-asparagine; the most common form is N-acetylglucosaminyl asparagine; N-acetylgalactosaminyl asparagine and N4 glucosyl asparagine also occur. This modification typically occurs in extracellular peptides with an N-X-(ST) motif. Partial modification has been observed to occur with cysteine, rather than serine or threonine, in the third position; secondary structure features are important, and proline in the second or fourth positions inhibits modification.\" [GOC:jsg]\ncomment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term is equivalent to protein N-linked glycosylation.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid N-linked glycosylation via asparagine\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30880\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0006487\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0018317\nname: obsolete protein C-linked glycosylation via tryptophan\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The glycosylation of a carbon atom of a peptidyl-tryptophan residue.\" [GOC:ai]\ncomment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term represents a molecular function.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid C-linked glycosylation via tryptophan\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29770\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0018103\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0018406\nname: obsolete protein C-linked glycosylation via 2'-alpha-mannosyl-L-tryptophan\nnamespace: biological_process\nalt_id: GO:0032004\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The glycosylation of a peptidyl-tryptophan residue by the transfer of alpha-mannopyranose from dolichyl-activated mannose to the indole ring.\" [PMID:7947762, PMID:9450955, RESID:AA0217]\ncomment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term represents a molecular function.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid C-linked glycosylation via 2'-alpha-mannosyl-L-tryptophan\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid C-linked mannosylation\" EXACT []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29770\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0018103\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0030210\nname: heparin proteoglycan biosynthetic process\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of heparin proteoglycans, which consist of a core protein linked to a heparin glycosaminoglycan. The heparin chain is composed of the repeating disaccharide unit beta-(1,4)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine-alpha-(1,4)-hexuronic acid, the former being either sulfated or deacetylated on its amino group as well as sulfated on one of its hydroxyl groups, and the latter being a mixture of sulfated and nonsulfated D-glucuronic and L-iduronic acids. Heparin is similar to heparan sulfate but it contains more N-sulfate and O-sulfate groups. Heparin chains are covalently linked to serine/threonine residues (O-linked) of the core protein via a tetrasaccharide linker sequence (xylose-galactose-galactose-glucuronate).\" [PMID:22566225]\nsynonym: \"heparan sulfate biosynthetic process\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"heparin anabolism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"heparin biosynthesis\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"heparin formation\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"heparin synthesis\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0180064 ! protein O-linked glycosylation via xylose\nintersection_of: GO:0009058 ! biosynthetic process\nintersection_of: has_primary_input CHEBI:233528 ! heparin proteoglycan\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28977\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29745\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30378\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0035269\nname: protein O-linked glycosylation via mannose\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A glycoprotein biosynthetic process starting with the covalent linkage of a mannose via an alpha-glycosidic bond to the oxygen atom of a serine or threonine side chain in a protein, which can be further elongated with the sequential addition of sugar units resulting in the formation of a protein O-linked glycan.\" [PMID:35536928]\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid O-linked mannosylation\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nsynonym: \"protein O-linked mannosylation\" RELATED []\nxref: MetaCyc:PWY-7921 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:PWY-7922 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:PWY-7979 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0006493 ! protein O-linked glycosylation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27107\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28527\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30362\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30592\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0036066\nname: protein O-linked glycosylation via fucose\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A glycoprotein biosynthetic process starting with the covalent linkage of a fucose via an alpha-glycosidic bond to the oxygen atom of a serine or threonine side chain in a protein, which can be further elongated with the sequential addition of sugar units resulting in the formation of a protein O-linked glycan. This modification typically occurs within specific motifs, such as EGF-like or thrombospondin type-1 repeats.\" [PMID:16899492, PMID:35536928]\nsynonym: \"protein O-linked fucosylation\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0006493 ! protein O-linked glycosylation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29770\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30255\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30362\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30592\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: bf\ncreation_date: 2011-12-15T11:17:20Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0042077\nname: obsolete protein phosphate-linked glycosylation via serine\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The glycosylation of peptidyl-serine through a phosphoester bond forming, for example, GlcNAc-alpha-1-P-Ser residues.\" [GOC:mah]\ncomment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term represents a molecular function.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid phosphate-linked glycosylation via serine\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29770\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0042543\nname: obsolete protein N-linked glycosylation via arginine\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The glycosylation of protein via peptidyl-arginine, omega-N-glycosyl-L-arginine.\" [RESID:AA0327]\ncomment: The reason for obsoletion is that these term were added in error\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-announcements/issues/822\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0006487\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0050650\nname: chondroitin sulfate proteoglycan biosynthetic process\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of chondroitin sulfate proteoglycans, which consist of a core protein linked to a chondroitin sulfate glycosaminoglycan. The chondroitin sulfate chain is composed of the repeating disaccharide unit beta-(1,4)-D-glucuronic acid-beta-(1,3)-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine, the latter of which can be O-sulfated. Chondroitin sulfate chains are covalently linked to serine/threonine residues (O-linked) of the core protein via a tetrasaccharide linker sequence (xylose-galactose-galactose-glucuronate).\" [PMID:17239763]\nsynonym: \"chondroitin sulfate proteoglycan anabolism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"chondroitin sulfate proteoglycan biosynthesis\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"chondroitin sulfate proteoglycan formation\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"chondroitin sulfate proteoglycan synthesis\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"chondroitin sulphate proteoglycan biosynthesis\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"chondroitin sulphate proteoglycan biosynthetic process\" EXACT []\nxref: MetaCyc:PWY-6567\nis_a: GO:0180064 ! protein O-linked glycosylation via xylose\nintersection_of: GO:0009058 ! biosynthetic process\nintersection_of: has_primary_output CHEBI:26349 ! chondroitin sulfate proteoglycan\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29294\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29745\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30378\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0050651\nname: dermatan sulfate proteoglycan biosynthetic process\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of dermatan sulfate proteoglycans, which consist of a core protein linked to a dermatan sulfate glycosaminoglycan. The dermatan sulfate chain is composed of the repeating disaccharide unit beta-(1,4)-D-hexuronic acid-beta-(1,3)-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine. Tthe former can be a mixture of sulfated and nonsulfated D-glucuronic and L-iduronic acids, and the latter can be O-sulfated. Dermatan sulfate chains are covalently linked to serine/threonine residues (O-linked) of the core protein via a tetrasaccharide linker sequence (xylose-galactose-galactose-glucuronate).\" [PMID:17239763]\nsynonym: \"chondroitin sulfate B proteoglycan biosynthesis\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"chondroitin sulfate B proteoglycan biosynthetic process\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"dermatan sulfate proteoglycan anabolism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"dermatan sulfate proteoglycan biosynthesis\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"dermatan sulfate proteoglycan formation\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"dermatan sulfate proteoglycan synthesis\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"dermatan sulphate proteoglycan biosynthesis\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"dermatan sulphate proteoglycan biosynthetic process\" EXACT []\nxref: MetaCyc:PWY-6568\nis_a: GO:0180064 ! protein O-linked glycosylation via xylose\nintersection_of: GO:0009058 ! biosynthetic process\nintersection_of: has_primary_output CHEBI:64602 ! dermatan sulfate proteoglycan\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29745\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30378\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0071903\nname: obsolete protein N-linked N-acetylglucosaminylation via asparagine\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. A process of protein N-linked glycosylation via asparagine in which N-acetylglucosamine is added to the N4 of asparagine, forming an (S)-2-amino-4-(2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranosyl)amino-4-oxobutanoic acid residue.\" [GOC:pr, RESID:AA0151]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents a molecular function.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid N-linked N-acetylglucosaminylation via asparagine\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28482\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\ncreated_by: mah\ncreation_date: 2010-09-15T03:49:16Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0071904\nname: obsolete protein N-linked N-acetylgalactosaminylation via asparagine\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. A process of protein N-linked glycosylation via asparagine in which N-acetylgalactosamine is added to the N4 of asparagine, forming an (S)-2-amino-4-(2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-galactopyranosyl)amino-4-oxobutanoic acid residue.\" [GOC:pr, RESID:AA0420]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents a molecular function.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid N-linked N-acetylgalactosaminylation via asparagine\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28482\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\ncreated_by: mah\ncreation_date: 2010-09-15T03:52:28Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0071905\nname: obsolete protein N-linked glucosylation via asparagine\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. A process of protein N-linked glycosylation via asparagine in which glucose is added to the N4 of asparagine, forming an (S)-2-amino-4-(D-glucopyranosyl)amino-4-oxobutanoic acid residue.\" [GOC:pr, RESID:AA0421]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents a molecular function.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid N-linked glucosylation via asparagine\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28482\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\ncreated_by: mah\ncreation_date: 2010-09-15T03:54:25Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0120532\nname: glycosaminoglycan-protein linkage region biosynthetic process\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The formation of a tetrasaccharide linker sequence (xylose-galactose-galactose-glucuronate) on specific serine residues of a core protein, on to which dermatan sulfate, chondroitin sulfate, heparan sulfate or heparin glycosaminoglycans may be assembled to synthesise the corresponding proteoglycan.\" [MetaCyc:PWY-6557]\nsynonym: \"Glycosaminoglycan biosynthesis, linkage tetrasaccharide\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"glycosaminoglycan-protein linkage region biosynthesis\" EXACT [MetaCyc:PWY-6557]\nxref: MetaCyc:PWY-6557\nis_a: GO:0180064 ! protein O-linked glycosylation via xylose\nrelationship: part_of GO:0015012 ! heparan sulfate proteoglycan 