er_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30140\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30595\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: vw\ncreation_date: 2025-06-02T08:07:11Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0180059\nname: protein O-linked glycosylation via glucose\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A glycoprotein biosynthetic process starting with the covalent linkage of a glucose via a beta-glycosidic bond to the oxygen atom of a serine, threonine or tyrosine side chain in a protein, which can be further elongated with the sequential addition of sugar units resulting in the formation of a protein O-linked glycan.\" [PMID:35536928]\nsynonym: \"protein O-linked glucosylation\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0006493 ! protein O-linked glycosylation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29770\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30362\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30592\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: vw\ncreation_date: 2025-06-03T08:20:06Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0180062\nname: protein O-linked glycosylation via galactose\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A glycoprotein biosynthetic process starting with the covalent linkage of galactose via a beta-glycosidic bond to the oxygen atom of the hydroxyl group of a hydroxyproline, a hydroxylysine, a serine or a threonine in a protein, which can be further elongated with the sequential addition of sugar units resulting in the formation of a protein O-linked glycan. Hydroxylysine modification occurs in the endoplasmic reticulum and is predominantly found in collagen. Hydroxyproline modification occurs in the Golgi and is found only in plant proteins.\" [PMID:17516569, PMID:30822656, PMID:33815452]\nsynonym: \"protein O-linked galactosylation\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0006493 ! protein O-linked glycosylation\np