{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778988340651,"sessionID":"ses_1cc096886ffecc0Y719VOrNnWp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_YJIxdgmKrUETvi0nVD99dLSf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+## Relevant pattern\n+\n+Issue: #32044 requests a new biological process term for O-GlcNAc addition to proteins.\n+\n+Observed GO precedent in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`:\n+\n+- `GO:0016266` protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetyl-galactosamine\n+- `GO:0035269` protein O-linked glycosylation via mannose\n+- `GO:0036066` protein O-linked glycosylation via fucose\n+- `GO:0180059` protein O-linked glycosylation via glucose\n+- `GO:0180062` protein O-linked glycosylation via galactose\n+- `GO:0180063` protein O-linked glycosylation via arabinose\n+- `GO:0180064` protein O-linked glycosylation via xylose\n+\n+Pattern conclusion:\n+\n+- These terms are modeled as direct `is_a` children of `GO:0006493` protein O-linked glycosylation.\n+- They generally do not use `intersection_of` axioms for the simple sugar-specific child term.\n+- Definitions follow a shared textual pattern: start with covalent linkage of the named sugar to the oxygen atom of an amino-acid side chain in a protein, sometimes followed by whether elongation can occur.\n+\n+Application to requested term:\n+\n+- New term should be a direct child of `GO:0006493`.\n+- No logical definition is required.\n+- The text definition should reflect the biology of O-GlcNAc specifically: a single beta-linked N-acetylglucosamine added to serine or threonine, without elongation to a larger oligosaccharide chain.\n*** Add File: RESEARCH.md\n+## PMID:35536957 \"The O-GlcNAc Modification.\"\n+\n+This review chapter supports treating O-GlcNAcylation as a distinct protein modification in which a single beta-linked N-acetylglucosamine is attached to serine or threonine residues on proteins. It also supports the statement that the modification is dynamic and widespread on intracellular proteins.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:35536957 \"This chapter presents an overview of the dynamic modification of serine or threonine hydroxyl moieties on nuclear, mitochondrial, and cytoplasmic proteins by O-linked beta-N-acetylglucosamine, termed O-beta-GlcNAc or simply O-GlcNAc.\"\n+    - O-GlcNAc is a protein modification on serine or threonine residues.\n+    - The attached sugar is O-linked beta-N-acetylglucosamine.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:35536957 \"This seemingly simple carbohydrate modification plays key roles in cellular physiology and disease progression.\"\n+    - The modification is treated in the literature as a distinct biological process, despite involving addition of only a single sugar.\n+\n+Term-crafting conclusion:\n+\n+- A GO biological process term for protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine is biologically justified.\n+- The definition should explicitly say the sugar is a single N-acetylglucosamine and is not elongated into a larger oligosaccharide chain.\n*** Add File: terms/GO_7770074.obo\n+[Term]\n+id: GO:7770074\n+name: protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine\n+namespace: biological_process\n+def: \"A glycoprotein biosynthetic process starting with the covalent linkage of a single N-acetylglucosamine via a beta-glycosidic bond to the oxygen atom of a serine or a threonine side chain in a protein, resulting in the formation of a protein O-linked glycan. The sugar is not elongated into a larger oligosaccharide chain.\" [PMID:35536957]\n+synonym: \"protein O-linked GlcNAcylation\" EXACT []\n+synonym: \"protein O-linked-N-acetylglucosaminylation\" EXACT []\n+is_a: GO:0006493 ! protein O-linked glycosylation\n+property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/32044\" xsd:anyURI\n+created_by: dragon-ai-agent\n+creation_date: 2026-05-17T03:25:02Z\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\nA RESEARCH.md\nA terms/GO_7770074.obo","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,25 @@\n+## Relevant pattern\n+\n+Issue: #32044 requests a new biological process term for O-GlcNAc addition to proteins.\n+\n+Observed GO precedent in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`:\n+\n+- `GO:0016266` protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetyl-galactosamine\n+- `GO:0035269` protein O-linked glycosylation via mannose\n+- `GO:0036066` protein O-linked glycosylation via fucose\n+- `GO:0180059` protein O-linked glycosylation via glucose\n+- `GO:0180062` protein O-linked glycosylation via galactose\n+- `GO:0180063` protein O-linked glycosylation via arabinose\n+- `GO:0180064` protein O-linked glycosylation via xylose\n+\n+Pattern conclusion:\n+\n+- These terms are modeled as direct `is_a` children of `GO:0006493` protein O-linked glycosylation.\n+- They generally do not use `intersection_of` axioms for the simple sugar-specific child term.\n+- Definitions follow a shared textual pattern: start with covalent linkage of the named sugar to the oxygen atom of an amino-acid side chain in a protein, sometimes followed by whether elongation can occur.\n+\n+Application to requested term:\n+\n+- New term should be a direct child of `GO:0006493`.\n+- No logical definition is required.\n+- The text definition should reflect the biology of O-GlcNAc specifically: a single beta-linked N-acetylglucosamine added to serine or threonine, without elongation to a larger oligosaccharide chain.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,15 @@\n+## PMID:35536957 \"The O-GlcNAc Modification.\"\n+\n+This review chapter supports treating O-GlcNAcylation as a distinct protein modification in which a single beta-linked N-acetylglucosamine is attached to serine or threonine residues on proteins. It also supports the statement that the modification is dynamic and widespread on intracellular proteins.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:35536957 \"This chapter presents an overview of the dynamic modification of serine or threonine hydroxyl moieties on nuclear, mitochondrial, and cytoplasmic proteins by O-linked beta-N-acetylglucosamine, termed O-beta-GlcNAc or simply O-GlcNAc.\"\n+    - O-GlcNAc is a protein modification on serine or threonine residues.\n+    - The attached sugar is O-linked beta-N-acetylglucosamine.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:35536957 \"This seemingly simple carbohydrate modification plays key roles in cellular physiology and disease progression.\"\n+    - The modification is treated in the literature as a distinct biological process, despite involving addition of only a single sugar.\n+\n+Term-crafting conclusion:\n+\n+- A GO biological process term for protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine is biologically justified.\n+- The definition should explicitly say the sugar is a single N-acetylglucosamine and is not elongated into a larger oligosaccharide chain.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770074.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770074.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770074.obo\n@@ -0,0 +1,11 @@\n+[Term]\n+id: GO:7770074\n+name: protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine\n+namespace: biological_process\n+def: \"A glycoprotein biosynthetic process starting with the covalent linkage of a single N-acetylglucosamine via a beta-glycosidic bond to the oxygen atom of a serine or a threonine side chain in a protein, resulting in the formation of a protein O-linked glycan. The sugar is not elongated into a larger oligosaccharide chain.\" [PMID:35536957]\n+synonym: \"protein O-linked GlcNAcylation\" EXACT []\n+synonym: \"protein O-linked-N-acetylglucosaminylation\" EXACT []\n+is_a: GO:0006493 ! protein O-linked glycosylation\n+property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/32044\" xsd:anyURI\n+created_by: dragon-ai-agent\n+creation_date: 2026-05-17T03:25:02Z\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","relativePath":"DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,25 @@\n+## Relevant pattern\n+\n+Issue: #32044 requests a new biological process term for O-GlcNAc addition to proteins.\n+\n+Observed GO precedent in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`:\n+\n+- `GO:0016266` protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetyl-galactosamine\n+- `GO:0035269` protein O-linked glycosylation via mannose\n+- `GO:0036066` protein O-linked glycosylation via fucose\n+- `GO:0180059` protein O-linked glycosylation via glucose\n+- `GO:0180062` protein O-linked glycosylation via galactose\n+- `GO:0180063` protein O-linked glycosylation via arabinose\n+- `GO:0180064` protein O-linked glycosylation via xylose\n+\n+Pattern conclusion:\n+\n+- These terms are modeled as direct `is_a` children of `GO:0006493` protein O-linked glycosylation.\n+- They generally do not use `intersection_of` axioms for the simple sugar-specific child term.\n+- Definitions follow a shared textual pattern: start with covalent linkage of the named sugar to the oxygen atom of an amino-acid side chain in a protein, sometimes followed by whether elongation can occur.\n+\n+Application to requested term:\n+\n+- New term should be a direct child of `GO:0006493`.\n+- No logical definition is required.\n+- The text definition should reflect the biology of O-GlcNAc specifically: a single beta-linked N-acetylglucosamine added to serine or threonine, without elongation to a larger oligosaccharide chain.\n","additions":25,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md","relativePath":"RESEARCH.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,15 @@\n+## PMID:35536957 \"The O-GlcNAc Modification.\"\n+\n+This review chapter supports treating O-GlcNAcylation as a distinct protein modification in which a single beta-linked N-acetylglucosamine is attached to serine or threonine residues on proteins. It also supports the statement that the modification is dynamic and widespread on intracellular proteins.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:35536957 \"This chapter presents an overview of the dynamic modification of serine or threonine hydroxyl moieties on nuclear, mitochondrial, and cytoplasmic proteins by O-linked beta-N-acetylglucosamine, termed O-beta-GlcNAc or simply O-GlcNAc.\"\n+    - O-GlcNAc is a protein modification on serine or threonine residues.\n+    - The attached sugar is O-linked beta-N-acetylglucosamine.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:35536957 \"This seemingly simple carbohydrate modification plays key roles in cellular physiology and disease progression.\"\n+    - The modification is treated in the literature as a distinct biological process, despite involving addition of only a single sugar.\n+\n+Term-crafting conclusion:\n+\n+- A GO biological process term for protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine is biologically justified.\n+- The definition should explicitly say the sugar is a single N-acetylglucosamine and is not elongated into a larger oligosaccharide chain.\