{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778988825662,"sessionID":"ses_1cc096886ffecc0Y719VOrNnWp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_VFIgPVoHSagyiLACyqexjZqM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Added the requested BP term `protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine` as a child of `protein O-linked glycosylation`, with synonyms for `protein O-linked GlcNAcylation` and `protein O-linked-N-acetylglucosaminylation`.\n+\n+The definition was based on PMID:35536957 and explicitly notes that this modification adds a single beta-linked N-acetylglucosamine to serine or threonine and is not elongated into a larger oligosaccharide chain.\n+\n+Changes committed locally and ready for PR #<NN>.\n*** Add File: PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Added a new biological process term to support annotation of Ogt/Eogt and orthologs at the requested level of granularity:\n+\n+- `GO:7770074` protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine\n+\n+What changed:\n+\n+- Added the new term under `GO:0006493` protein O-linked glycosylation.\n+- Added exact synonyms:\n+  - `protein O-linked GlcNAcylation`\n+  - `protein O-linked-N-acetylglucosaminylation`\n+- Added `term_tracker_item` linking back to issue `#32044`.\n+- Added `created_by` and `creation_date` metadata for the new term.\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- The issue requests a BP term for O-GlcNAcylation so relevant gene products can be annotated more specifically than the generic parent `protein O-linked glycosylation`.\n+- Existing GO precedent under `protein O-linked glycosylation` models sugar-specific child processes as direct `is_a` descendants without adding extra logical axioms.\n+- PMID:35536957 supports the biology captured in the definition: O-GlcNAc is a distinct modification of serine/threonine residues by a single beta-linked N-acetylglucosamine.\n+\n+Validation and research performed:\n+\n+- Validated PMID:35536957 with `linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:35536957`.\n+- Created temporary `RESEARCH.md` and `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md` notes to document literature support and GO modeling precedent.\n+- Validated supporting text in `RESEARCH.md` with `linkml-reference-validator validate text-file`.\n+- Ran `make travis_build` from `src/ontology`; build passed.\n+\n+Completed checklist:\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: The issue and all its context has been analyzed, the intent is clear, and a plan for addressing it has been created\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: Current state of the ontology validates prior to any changes\n+- [x] RESEARCH: Necessary background research performed and captured in `RESEARCH.md`\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: Relevant ontology terms were consulted in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: Existing design patterns and sibling terms were consulted and summarized in `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md`\n+- [x] EDITS: Correct new-term procedure followed using a staging file in `terms/` and `obo-checkin.pl`\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: Appropriate parentage included\n+- [x] logical definitions are appropriate, and are not over-specified, and conform to DESIGN_PATTERNS.md doc\n+- [x] relationships conform to other similar terms in the ontology\n+- [x] is_a is not over-asserted\n+- [x] is_a, part_of, and other relationships specified appropriately\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: `/chemical-entity` and `/design-pattern` consulted; no extra CHEBI axiom or DP logical definition was needed for this BP term\n+- [x] METADATA: New-term metadata included and issue link added\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: Ontology validates with `make travis_build`\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: PMID:35536957 validated and used for the definition\n+- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED\n+- [x] RELEVANT-FILES: Only `src/ontology/go-edit.obo` was committed\n+- [x] ACCURACY: The change is biologically aligned with the cited review and existing GO precedent\n+- [x] ISSUE-ALIGNMENT: The change addresses the requested new term coherently\n+- [ ] PR is created or amended\n+- [x] Communicate high level summary of changes on original issue(s), and any requests for further info\n+- [x] Communicated on PR detailed description of changes made, and rationale. Include checklists.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@\n+Added the requested BP term `protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine` as a child of `protein O-linked glycosylation`, with synonyms for `protein O-linked GlcNAcylation` and `protein O-linked-N-acetylglucosaminylation`.\n+\n+The definition was based on PMID:35536957 and explicitly notes that this modification adds a single beta-linked N-acetylglucosamine to serine or threonine and is not elongated into a larger oligosaccharide chain.\n+\n+Changes committed locally and ready for PR #<NN>.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,50 @@\n+Added a new biological process term to support annotation of Ogt/Eogt and orthologs at the requested level of granularity:\n+\n+- `GO:7770074` protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine\n+\n+What changed:\n+\n+- Added the new term under `GO:0006493` protein O-linked glycosylation.\n+- Added exact synonyms:\n+  - `protein O-linked GlcNAcylation`\n+  - `protein O-linked-N-acetylglucosaminylation`\n+- Added `term_tracker_item` linking back to issue `#32044`.\n+- Added `created_by` and `creation_date` metadata for the new term.\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- The issue requests a BP term for O-GlcNAcylat